WEBVTT



00:00:00.992 --> 00:00:05.024
This sermon is brought to you by Buford Road Baptist Church.

00:00:04.800 --> 00:00:08.160
the speaker today is Pastor Tony Kahoot

00:00:08.640 --> 00:00:10.176
I want to read

00:00:10.400 --> 00:00:13.120
what we call the Christmas story to you

00:00:13.536 --> 00:00:16.352
Out of the Gospel of Luke, Chapter 2.

00:00:16.864 --> 00:00:18.112
And?

00:00:18.464 --> 00:00:22.080
This has always been something very special in our home.

00:00:23.136 --> 00:00:26.624
Since I can remember as a child on Christmas morning,

00:00:27.200 --> 00:00:30.976
We would always turn to this text and we would read this

00:00:30.976 --> 00:00:32.704
Portion of Scripture,

00:00:33.056 --> 00:00:36.672
Before any presence of any sort were exchanged,

00:00:37.216 --> 00:00:39.008
And we have

00:00:39.552 --> 00:00:42.880
Carried this tradition on from our childhood into.

00:00:43.008 --> 00:00:48.096
Our our family's life and I'm glad to know that they still do this.

00:00:48.512 --> 00:00:50.656
Together as well.

00:00:51.008 --> 00:00:54.016
And I don't think that we could really.

00:00:55.136 --> 00:01:00.576
End of service, or get to the close to the end without reading these wonderful blessed words.

00:01:01.984 --> 00:01:05.664
And so let me read for you tonight in Luke, Chapter two.

00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:08.640
Beginning in verse number one.

00:01:10.080 --> 00:01:15.584
And it came to pass in those days that there went out a decree from Caesar Augustus.

00:01:16.320 --> 00:01:18.752
That all the world should be taxed,

00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:24.480
And this taxing was first made when Cyrenius was governor of Syria.

00:01:25.344 --> 00:01:27.552
And all went to be taxed

00:01:27.904 --> 00:01:30.272
Everyone into his own city.

00:01:31.232 --> 00:01:35.776
And Joseph also went up from Galilee, out of the city of Nazareth,

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.704
Into Judea, unto the city of David, which is called Bethlehem.

00:01:41.088 --> 00:01:44.192
Because it was of the house and lineage of David.

00:01:44.640 --> 00:01:49.120
To be taxed with Mary, his espoused wife, being great with child.

00:01:49.696 --> 00:01:52.768
And so it was that while they were there,

00:01:53.088 --> 00:01:57.376
The days were accomplished that she should be delivered.

00:01:58.016 --> 00:02:04.320
And she brought forth her firstborn son, and wrapped him in swaddling clothes, and laid him in a manger.

00:02:04.576 --> 00:02:07.488
Because there was no room for them in the inn.

00:02:08.224 --> 00:02:12.160
And there were in the same country shepherds abiding in the field.

00:02:12.640 --> 00:02:15.360
Keeping watch over their flock by night.

00:02:16.096 --> 00:02:22.944
And lo, the angel of the Lord came upon them,, and the glory of the Lord shone round about them,, and they were sore afraid.

00:02:23.808 --> 00:02:26.656
And the angel said unto them, Fear not.

00:02:27.488 --> 00:02:32.576
For behold, I bring you good tidings of great joy, which shall be to all people.

00:02:33.312 --> 00:02:37.504
For unto you is born this day in the city of David a saviour,

00:02:37.920 --> 00:02:39.840
Which is Christ the Lord,

00:02:40.864 --> 00:02:43.264
And this shall be a sign unto you.

00:02:43.744 --> 00:02:48.352
You shall find the babe wrapped in swaddling clothes, lying in a manger.

00:02:48.928 --> 00:02:52.480
And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude.

00:02:52.704 --> 00:02:57.888
Of the heavenly host praising God and saying, glory to God in the highest.

00:02:58.112 --> 00:02:59.520
And on earth,

00:02:59.744 --> 00:03:00.896
Peace,

00:03:00.896 --> 00:03:02.784
Good-will toward men!

00:03:03.424 --> 00:03:10.112
And it came to pass, as the angels were gone away from them into heaven, the shepherds said one to another.

00:03:10.688 --> 00:03:13.920
Let us now go even unto Bethlehem.

00:03:14.304 --> 00:03:19.552
And see this thing which is come to pass, which the Lord hath made known unto us.

00:03:20.128 --> 00:03:25.344
And they came with haste, and found Mary and Joseph, and the babe lying in a manger.

00:03:25.856 --> 00:03:27.648
And when they had seen it,

00:03:28.096 --> 00:03:32.928
They made known abroad the saying which was told them concerning this child.

00:03:33.728 --> 00:03:39.392
And all they that heard it wondered at those things which were told them by the shepherds.

00:03:40.224 --> 00:03:44.160
But Mary kept all these things and pondered them in her heart.

00:03:44.768 --> 00:03:50.592
And the shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God for all the things that they had heard.

00:03:50.784 --> 00:03:53.248
And seen as it was told,,

00:03:53.472 --> 00:03:54.880
Unto them.

00:04:06.720 --> 00:04:08.704
And we do want to wish you.

00:04:09.216 --> 00:04:12.512
All of very, very Merry Christmas.

00:04:13.472 --> 00:04:16.096
And a very happy prosperous new year.

00:04:17.344 --> 00:04:20.928
And I do pray that you would keep Christ in the center

00:04:21.216 --> 00:04:23.520
Of all of your activities

00:04:23.936 --> 00:04:26.016
All of your festivities.

00:04:26.944 --> 00:04:29.792
Tomorrow I'd like to encourage you to

00:04:30.560 --> 00:04:35.072
Maybe perhaps pick up a tradition if you have not done it already.

00:04:35.968 --> 00:04:39.520
Before anything is celebrated or gifted.

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.480
You would take time to open the scriptures maybe with a cup of coffee

00:04:46.112 --> 00:04:48.448
And as you reflect on

00:04:48.960 --> 00:04:51.328
What this season is all about.

00:04:52.256 --> 00:04:53.600
Take time,

00:04:54.592 --> 00:04:56.736
To thank god in heaven.

00:04:57.536 --> 00:04:59.584
For sending Jesus.

00:05:00.128 --> 00:05:02.880
To be the sacrifice for our soul.

00:05:04.096 --> 00:05:07.488
And the scripture says, though he was rich, he became poor.

00:05:08.448 --> 00:05:11.584
That through his poverty, we might be made rich.

00:05:13.440 --> 00:05:19.008
We remember the scriptures for the Son of Man has come to seek and to save that which was lost.

00:05:20.800 --> 00:05:22.368
Thank God.

00:05:23.296 --> 00:05:25.920
Even before this world was made,

00:05:27.520 --> 00:05:29.952
God chose to send Jesus.

00:05:30.720 --> 00:05:32.416
The lamb of God.

00:05:32.832 --> 00:05:36.000
Who was slain before the foundation of this world.

00:05:37.184 --> 00:05:38.880
To go to the cross.

00:05:39.264 --> 00:05:40.960
He shed his blood.

00:05:42.048 --> 00:05:45.216
For God would raise him gloriously from the dead.

00:05:45.984 --> 00:05:49.152
And by us putting our faith and our trust

00:05:49.312 --> 00:05:51.072
In the Lord Jesus.

00:05:51.872 --> 00:05:56.736
The Bible says, for whosoever shall call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.

00:05:57.632 --> 00:06:03.904
I'm thankful tonight that we can stand here together as born-again believers in the faith.

00:06:04.864 --> 00:06:06.976
Knowing whom we had the means.

00:06:07.904 --> 00:06:11.648
Knowing that there is an empty tomb and a risen savior.

00:06:13.440 --> 00:06:15.424
And the Christ of Christmas.

00:06:16.192 --> 00:06:17.920
It's truly our mistake.

00:06:19.456 --> 00:06:21.088
May you be blessed.

00:06:21.504 --> 00:06:22.880
Tonight

00:06:23.136 --> 00:06:24.352
Tomorrow

00:06:24.832 --> 00:06:26.976
And then this brand new year to come.

00:06:28.512 --> 00:06:29.792
We love you.

00:06:30.368 --> 00:06:33.280
We thank God for every home and family.

00:06:33.760 --> 00:06:37.440
That makes up the congregation of Beaufort Road Baptist Church.

00:06:38.400 --> 00:06:41.280
you listen to Pastor Tony Kahoot

00:06:41.184 --> 00:06:47.296
For more information, visit our website at bufordrodebaptistchurch.com
